The Federal Government has said it has recorded improved security situation across the country within the third quarter of 2019. The Inspector General of Police, Muhammed Adamu briefing State House Correspondents today in Abuja after a Security meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari noted that the decline in kidnapping, banditry and other forms of criminality, was due to several peace initiatives by government.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that according to the IGP, In June a total of 111 murder cases were reported nationally, while it reduced to 99 in July and 80cases in August, adding that 183 armed robbery incidents were recorded in June with the rate dropping to 127 in July and 93 in August this year. The IGP further stated that similar decline was recorded in rate of Kidnapping, with 112 in July and further decline to 83 in August this year.  The IGP added the Close Circuit Monitors and regular police patrols are in place to help check crime in the Federal Capital Territory while assuring the security agents commitment to protecting the lives and properties of citizens.